[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorcyclist dies in A449 crash between Coldra and Usk

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorcyclist has died in a collision with a car in Monmouthshire, say Gwent Police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The crash, which involved a white Kawasaki motorbike and a black BMW car, happened on the northbound section of the A449 between Coldra and Usk.
The alarm was raised at 11:15 BST on Saturday and an air ambulance was called but the man was pronounced dead at the scene.
The road is closed as investigations into the incident start.
Gwent Police are appealing for witnesses to contact them, quoting log number 202.
